    "type": "message",
    "text": "_#past-company_\n\nWhen the industry switched over from mainframes and minicomputers to personal computers, how big a regression was the performance of a typical PC versus that of a mainframe / mini at the time? (Keeping this question vague because I'm not quite sure how to phrase it. Feel free to interpret it however you like.)",
    "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "ts": "1688076426.176689",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "=iUv",
        "elements": [
