                "type": "text",
                "text": "#past-company",
                "style": {
                  "italic": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\nWhen the industry switched over from mainframes and minicomputers to personal computers, how big a regression was the performance of a typical PC versus that of a mainframe / mini at the time? (Keeping this question vague because I'm not quite sure how to phrase it. Feel free to interpret it however you like.)"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
